   LIMA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Alfonso Bustamante, Peru's premier and trade and industry minister, has
resigned following last week's move by parliament and the executive against
the autonomy of the Supreme Court, writes Sally Bowen in Lima.
Mr Efrain Goldenberg, a businessman who has headed the foreign ministry for
rather less than six months, replaces Mr Bustamante as premier. Mr
Goldenberg joined the cabinet last September with no previous political
background and no experience of diplomacy.
