<HEADLINE>
FT  18 FEB 94 / UN inspectors in Baghdad
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MANAMA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
United Nations inspectors yesterday arrived in Baghdad to visit military
plants to prepare for long-term UN control and monitoring of Iraq's arms
industry, Reuter reports from Manama. The 14 UN experts will visit a dozen
military production facilities around Baghdad during their nine-day stay.
The UN Special Commission dismantling Iraqi weapons under 1991 Gulf
ceasefire terms is stepping up pressure to enforce UN resolution 715
preventing Baghdad from re-establishing its previous nuclear, chemical,
biological and long-range missile potential.
