<HEADLINE>
FT  18 FEB 94 / Arab-Israeli clashes result in more fatalities
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID HOROVITZ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JERUSALEM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
In a spate of Israeli-Arab clashes yesterday, an Israeli soldier shot dead a
Palestinian man at an army checkpoint near Jenin in the West Bank, and an
Israeli guard at a building site in the southern port town of Ashdod was
stabbed to death, apparently by a Palestinian, writes David Horovitz in
Jerusalem. Another Israeli, stabbed by Palestinian militants near Hebron six
weeks ago, died of his wounds yesterday. And at least four Palestinians were
shot and wounded in clashes with the army in the West Bank town of Halhoul.
</TEXT>
