Neiman Marcus, the US fashion retailer, lifted net profits by 22 per cent to
Dollars 21.5m in its second quarter to January 29, helped by strong sales in
its Neiman Marcus and Bergdorf Goodman stores and NM Direct catalogue
division.
The company said the stores and catalogue had a particularly good Christmas,
