to 37 cents from 27 cents. For the first six months, net income rose to
Dollars 36.7m from Dollars 33.7m and earnings per share to 58 cents from 51
cents.
Mr Robert Tarr, president and chief executive, said the company expected the
usual net loss in the second half.
