<TEXT>
Newbridge Networks, a fast-growing Ottawa digital transmission equipment
maker, more than doubled third-quarter profit and said demand continued to
be strong.
Third-quarter net profit, which was better than expected, rose to CDollars
41.4m (USDollars 31.4m), or 52 cents a share, up from CDollars 17.7m, or 24
cents, a year earlier, on sales of CDollars 145m, up 73 per cent.
Nine-month profit advanced to CDollars 110.5m, or CDollars 1.39, from
CDollars 34.5m, or 48 cents, on revenues of CDollars 388m, a leap of 88 per
cent.
Teleglobe, Canada's overseas telecommunications utility, earned CDollars
75.5m, or CDollars 1.20 a share, in 1993, against a loss of CDollars 50.6m,
or CDollars 1.19, after special charges in 1992. Revenues were CDollars
1.4bn, up 18 per cent. International telephone traffic gained 12.5 per cent
in 1993.
