FT  17 FEB 94 / International Company News: Burns Philps earnings rise to
ADollars 76.3m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Burns Philps, the Australian food and hardware retailing company which has
been restructuring around its food and food ingredients division, yesterday
reported a 40 per cent increase in profits after tax in the six months to
end-December, to ADollars 76.3m (USDollars 54.5m) from ADollars 54.5m.
The company said it was still preparing to float its hardware retailing
division on the stock market, but would consider a trade sale of the
business if this was in the interests of shareholders. It said earnings
before tax interest and tax from its hardware division were up by 55 per
cent at ADollars 27.7m.
