FT  17 FEB 94 / Girobank services 'not hit by strike'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Girobank said last night that the 24-hour strike by its clerical staff did
not appear to have affected customer services.
The bank said most of the 2,200 staff at its Bootle headquarters on
Merseyside backed the dispute but many worked normally at the bank's other
offices.
The NCU communications union warned that regular 24-hour strikes would
continue until Girobank management improved its 1.5 per cent consolidated
pay offer. The two sides are due to meet before the next strike, planned for
March 8.
