<HEADLINE>
FT  17 FEB 94 / End urged for binding-over
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Court powers to 'bind over' a person to keep the peace or 'be of good
behaviour' should be abolished, the Law Commission said yesterday.
The government's law reform body said the 'archaic power' offends against
modern notions of justice and human rights.
A person can be bound over without being convicted of an offence, and
although people cannot be bound over without their consent, they may be
jailed if they refuse to give it.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
