<HEADLINE>
FT  17 FEB 94 / World Trade News: Russia, US sign accord on drugs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US and Russia have signed an agreement to give US pharmaceutical
companies speedier and greater access to the Russian market, the White House
said yesterday, Reuter reports from Washington.
It said that Russia's Ministry of Health and Medical Industry would allow
the import of US-approved and US-made drugs without additional clinical
trials and would limit its review period to 90 days.
The White House said that in effect medications meeting US standards would
get nearly automatic entry into Russia. It said the agreement was signed in
Washington last month and in Moscow on Tuesday.
