<TEXT>
Japanese officials were yesterday dismayed at the US finding that Japan has
violated agreements to open up its cellular phone market, Michiyo Nakamoto
writes.
Mr Takenori Kanzaki, minister of posts and telecommunications, denied the US
allegation that Japan had failed to live up to its promise to increase
market access for cellular phones and equipment made by Motorola.
