FT  17 FEB 94 / Poland clears way for IMF debt deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BOBINSKI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WARSAW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Poland's parliamentary budget committee yesterday approved the 1994 draft
budget, paving the way for an IMF-negotiated debt reduction programme with
the Paris Club of western creditors, writes Christopher Bobinski in Warsaw.
The Z83,000bn budget, already approved by the IMF, represents a public
deficit of 4.2 per cent of gross domestic product. It is central to the
IMF-negotiated agreement to reduce Poland's Dollars 33bn debt by 20 per
cent. The budget still has to go to the full chamber for approval but
yesterday's decision is likely to undermine a campaign on the left of the
governing coalition for higher spending.
