<HEADLINE>
FT  17 FEB 94 / Slovak PM faces rejection
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRATISLAVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Slovakia's parliament yesterday rejected a proposal by Prime Minister
Vladimir Meciar for early elections next June, Reuter reports from
Bratislava. Opposition deputies predicted the defeat of Meciar's proposal
would be followed by a vote of no confidence in his government within the
next few days.
